The First Lady Cultivates 'American Grown' Gardeningtoggle caption Pablo Martinez Monsivais/APOne of the first things Michelle Obama did as first lady was to dig up part of the beautifully manicured South Lawn of the White House and plant a vegetable garden.
Her latest project, a book called American Grown, is a diary of that garden through the seasons and a portrait of gardening in America, past and present.
